'''日本-琉球语系'''（{{lang-en|Japanese-Ryukyuan languages}}），或稱'''日本語系'''（{{lang-en|Japonic languages}}），是世界主要[[語系|語系]]之一，包含[[日語|日語]]和[[琉球語|琉球語]]两大分支，使用人口約1.25億。

==介紹==
关于'''[[日本語|日本語]]'''与其它[[语言|语言]]和[[语系|语系]]的关系到目前为止由学者们提出过许多理论:
*'''[[日琉語系|日琉語系]]'''：日琉語系這個概念最早由[[美國|美國]]的日本學者{{tsl|en|Leon Serafim|萊昂·塞拉芬}}提出<ref>Shimabukuro, Moriyo. (2007). ''The Accentual History of the Japanese and Ryukyuan Languages: a Reconstruction,'' p. 1.</ref>，後來這一概念受到國際語言學者的普遍接受，根據[[日琉同祖論|日琉同祖論]]，日琉語系的所有語言的[[祖語|祖語]]都是原始日語(Proto-Japonic)<ref>Miyake, Marc Hideo. (2008). {{google books|MkSDqluKPxsC|''Old Japanese: a Phonetic Reconstruction.'' p.的 66.|page=66}}</ref>。

*'''[[孤立語言|孤立語言]]'''：有些日本學者認為[[琉球語|琉球語]]是[[日語|日語]]的[[日語方言|方言]]，称之为琉球方言，但大部分语言学家认为[[日语|日语]]和[[琉球语|琉球语]]是两个属于同[[语系|语系]]但有很大区别的语言，各有各的方言。{{tsl|ja|服部四郎}}認為，日語和琉球語分化的時間為[[大和時代|大和時代]]<ref>Heinrich, Patrick. [http://www.sicri-network.org/ISIC1/j.%20ISIC1P%20Heinrich.pdf "What leaves a mark should no longer stain: Progressive erasure and reversing language shift activities in the Ryukyu Islands,"] {{Wayback|url=http://www.sicri-network.org/ISIC1/j.%20ISIC1P%20Heinrich.pdf |date=20110516043839 }} First International Small Island Cultures Conference at [[Kagoshima_University|Kagoshima University]], Centre for the Pacific Islands, February 7–10, 2005; citing [[Shiro_Hattori|Shiro Hattori]]. (1954) ''Gengo nendaigaku sunawachi goi tokeigaku no hoho ni tsuite'' ("Concerning the Method of Glottochronology and Lexicostatistics"), ''Gengo kenkyu'' (''Journal of the Linguistic Society of Japan''), Vols. 26/27.</ref>。

*'''[[澳台语系|澳台语系]]'''：[[南岛语|南岛语]]与日语也有类似点：[[元音|元音]](母音)有5个，即あ(a)、い(i)、う(u)、え(e)、お(o)，不使用[[元音|双重元音]]；[[单词|单词]]以元音结束；[[浊音|浊音]]不同于单词之首等，但日本語與[[南島語系|南島語系]]語言之間缺乏同源[[词汇|词汇]]。

*'''[[扶餘語系|扶餘語系]]'''：[[克里斯托弗·貝克威思|克里斯托弗·貝克威思]]提出了[[扶餘語系|扶餘語系]]的假說，認為[[高句麗語|高句麗語]]、[[百濟語|百濟語]]、[[新羅語|新羅語]]、[[古日語|古日語]]等古代語言可能同源。

*'''[[漢藏語系|漢藏語系]]'''：[[西田龍雄|西田龍雄]]認為日語屬於漢藏語系[[藏緬語族|藏緬語族]]。

*'''[[阿爾泰語系|阿爾泰語系]]'''：持阿爾泰[[超語系|超語系]]假說的人認為日語屬于[[阿爾泰語系|阿爾泰語系]]，但該語系已经在主流学术界上被否定<ref>"While 'Altaic' is repeated in encyclopedias and handbooks most specialists in these languages no longer believe that the three traditional supposed Altaic groups, Turkic, Mongolian and Tungusic, are related." Lyle Campbell & Mauricio J. Mixco, A Glossary of Historical Linguistics (2007, University of Utah Press), pg. 7.</ref><ref>"When cognates proved not to be valid, Altaic was abandoned, and the received view now is that Turkic, Mongolian, and Tungusic are unrelated." Johanna Nichols, Linguistic Diversity in Space and Time (1992, Chicago), pg. 4.</ref><ref>"Careful examination indicates that the established families, Turkic, Mongolian, and Tungusic, form a linguistic area (called Altaic)...Sufficient criteria have not been given that would justify talking of a genetic relationship here." R.M.W. Dixon, The Rise and Fall of Languages (1997, Cambridge), pg. 32.</ref><ref>"...[T]his selection of features does not provide good evidence for common descent" and "we can observe convergence rather than divergence between Turkic and Mongolic languages--a pattern than is easily explainable by borrowing and diffusion rather than common descent", Asya Pereltsvaig, Languages of the World, An Introduction (2012, Cambridge) has a good discussion of the Altaic hypothesis (pp. 211-216).</ref><ref>[http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayAbstract;jsessionid=A7D36A55C4A29AEB34AA39715F46F706.tomcat1?fromPage=online&aid=17033 Georg ''et al.'' 1999:] {{Wayback|url=http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayAbstract;jsessionid=A7D36A55C4A29AEB34AA39715F46F706.tomcat1?fromPage=online&aid=17033 |date=20160303180656 }} 73–74</ref>。不过，仍有少數學者支持存在这个语系<ref name=georg1999>Stefan Georg, Peter A. Michalove, Alexis Manaster Ramer, and Paul J. Sidwell (1999): "[http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayAbstract;jsessionid=A7D36A55C4A29AEB34AA39715F46F706.tomcat1?fromPage=online&aid=17033 Telling general linguists about Altaic] {{Wayback|url=http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayAbstract;jsessionid=A7D36A55C4A29AEB34AA39715F46F706.tomcat1?fromPage=online&aid=17033 |date=20160303180656 }}". ''Journal of Linguistics'', volume 35, issue 1, pages 65–98.</ref>。因此是否存在这个语系，学术界直到现在都存在争议。

*'''[[達羅毗荼語系|達羅毗荼語系]]'''：{{tsl|ja|大野晋}}認為日本語屬於[[達羅毗荼語系|達羅毗荼語系]]。

